title: For Sale:  Custom Wilson Combat CQB
postcontent:
Having moved to striker-fired pistols for carry, I have reluctantly decided to offer for sale a VERY nice custom Wilson Combat 1911 CQB in .45 ACP. This pistol started life in 2001 as a hand-fitted carbon steel CQB custom-built to my specs by Wilson Combat and finished in black Teflon. It was carried daily, but shot very sparingly.
After the Teflon finish finally began to show some holster wear it received an extensive further customization & refinish in 2012. Work done included hand-cut 25 LPI checkering on the frontstrap and mainspring housing, undercut trigger guard, flushed & beveled barrel crown, recessed & chamfered take-down pin, fresh Heine boot ledge straight 8 Tritium night sights, beautiful hard chrome finish by APW with brushed flats & satin rounds, VZ grips with custom screws.
There have been less than 500 rounds fired after the refinish, less than 1000 rounds total. Among extras included will be a tungsten recoil spring guide rod, 4 Wilson 47D magazines with fresh followers & springs, and a Wilson Combat pistol rug.
The slide to frame fit is perfect and the trigger is glass rod at 3#. You will rarely see a 1911 this nice. I have about $4000 in this one-of-a-kind custom Wilson Combat CQB, I will sell it for $3250. Bill of sale with DL # will be completed.
I am 45 minutes from Hattiesburg.     Dave REDACTED
